finish turning by hand a roughish draft, of some 80,000 words in all, into a fair copy which would gradually make, in regular batches, over 250 typed pages of "LOOK AT THE HARLEQUINS!"



After careful consideration I choose the second course, and send you my deepest apologies.





Sincerely yours,

Vladimir Nabokov





A statement by Vladimir Nabokov

